Hi Shane,

Thank you for meeting with us today! There is an R package for the physiology data on these rats. Will this work? https://motrpac.github.io/MotrpacRatTrainingPhysiologyData/

For phenotypes in the model I would start with:
-Change in Vo2max
-Change in % lean mass 
-plasma lactate
-plasma glycerol
-plasma NEFA

For the muscle specific phenotypes it gets a little tricky—the gastroc (GN in the omics data Nick sent) was phenotyped by region (termed LG and MG). If we use these measures, I would average values between LG and MG to associate with omes per animal given we used whole muscle samples (both regions) for omic analyses.  I was also thinking it would be good to add global proteomics to the analysis—this can help with sanity checks for known pathways and associated phenotypes. 

Additional phenotypes:
-LG/MG CSA
-LG/MG CS activity
-LG/MG Type I fibers
-LG/MG Type II fibers
-LG/MG glycogen
-insulin
-corticosterone
-glucagon
-glucose

If you need help identifying the phenotypes in the package, feel free to send me a message any time. 

Thank you so much for your help and have a nice weekend!

Gina
